The paper deals with power allocation in wireless systems, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of fixed beamformers and the consideration of QoS constraints suggest a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective. The paper also mentions the use of convex optimization techniques, which is a common tool in machine learning (cs.MM) and optimization (cs.LG).
